The paper discusses the use of complex datasets related to Wikipedia to study language, social behavior, knowledge organization, and network theory, which are all topics that fall under the Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), and Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-categories. The proposed data structure leverages principles of graph databases, which is a topic that falls under the Software Engineering (cs.SE) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of viewership statistics or "pagecounts" of Wikipedia web pages, which is a topic that falls under the Digital Libraries (cs.DL) and Computation and Language (cs.CL) sub-categories. Finally, the paper provides deployment guidelines, which is a topic that falls under the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category.
